ne of Orthodontic treatment and are the most used modality. Modern brackets are more smaller, less noticeable and are better tolerated by cheek and lips. Both metal and ceramic provide same treatment time, although the ceramic braces are preferred by many for their esthetic appeal.\n\n<strong id=\"selfligating-braces\">2. Self-ligating braces:</strong>  Damon self ligating brackets is the most modern system that uses lesser forces to provide more frictionless movement of teeth, when compared with traditional braces. The self ligation provides lesser friction between wire and bracket, allowing a slide movement that has lesser pressure on teeth and shortens the treatment time. These are available in metal and ceramic.\n\n<strong id=\"invisible-braces\">3. Lingual (invisible) braces:</strong>  They are similar to traditional braces, but the brackets and wires are attached behind the teeth, making it invisible. Highly recommended for individuals who prefer the treatment to remain inconspicuous.\n\n<strong id=\"invisalign\">4. Invisalign:</strong>  With nano and 3D printing technology advancing, it has provided a new array of treatment choices into Orthodontics. This system has a set of sequential removable clear aligners that are custom made for each individual designed to move their teeth. The aligners are changed into a newer set every 2 weeks providing new activation. These are convenient as they are almost invisible and are removed while eating. They are the perfect solution for people who find the look and feel of the traditional braces unappealing and discomforting.\n\n<strong id=\"inman-aligner\">5. Inman aligner:</strong>  This is a removable type of solution to correct mild to moderate malalignment and crowding. Although limited to correction range, the advantage is that the treatment is very short.\n\n<strong id=\"orthopedic-myofunctional\">6. Habit breaking and myofunctional appliances:</strong>  These are primarily for children and adolescent patients who require early intervention to correct prolonged habits and developing deformities in teeth and jaw bones.Prolonged Thumbsucking and tongue thrusting are common habits that cause effect on teeth and jaw. Myofuntional appliances are used for correcting bony defect such as protruding jaw and also in correction of short lower jaw.','Orthodontics','','inherit','closed','closed','','34-autosave-v1','','','2016-11-14 11:37:46','2016-11-14 11:37:46','',34,'http://silesia.dev/34-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(165,1,'2016-11-14 11:38:48','2016-11-14 11:38:48','','about','','inherit','open','closed','','about','','','2016-11-14 11:38:48','2016-11-14 11:38:48','',34,'http://silesia.dev/app/uploads/2016/11/about.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(166,1,'2016-11-14 11:42:48','2016-11-14 11:42:48','<h3>General Extractions</h3>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<p id=\"general-extraction\">When the teeth is beyond repair, it needs to be removed before it may cause a more severe sequelae that in turn gives rise to pain, swelling and discomfort. In some cases, it may be necessary to remove a tooth to facilitate Orthodontic treatment.</p>\r\nAt Silesia dental clinic, you are in expert hands who extract teeth with utmost care and almost painlessly. All extraction are done with local anaesthesia.\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-95\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/car-1284643_1280-1024x450.jpg\" alt=\"car-1284643_1280\" width=\"100%\" height=\"auto\" />[/one_half_last]\r\n<p id=\"general-extraction\"></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Surgical removal</h3>\r\n[one_half]<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-95\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/car-1284643_1280-1024x450.jpg\" alt=\"car-1284643_1280\" width=\"100%\" height=\"auto\" />[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<p id=\"surgical-removal\">This requires a surgical incision into the gum in order to access the indicated tooth to be removed. Most common are impacted wisdom teeth. They remain within the jaw bone and require to be removed surgically.</p>\r\nSutures may be placed for closure and healthier healing of the extraction site. Medications are prescribed for easing post operative discomforts, based on the extent of the procedure.\r\n\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n<p id=\"surgical-removal\"></p>','removing teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision-v1','','','2016-11-14 11:42:48','2016-11-14 11:42:48','',38,'http://silesia.dev/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(167,1,'2016-11-14 11:46:13','2016-11-14 11:46:13','<h3>FILLINGS</h3>\r\n[two_third]\r\n<p id=\"fillings\">Teeth cavitation is one of the most prevalent problems in the World. Its very influenced by diet, hygiene habits. It can lead to sensitivities, unbearable pain and further untreated defects can cause complications that may even lead to systemic problems.</p>\r\nDental caries need to be treated at the earliest. These are best treated at an early onset when the damage is not extensive. In a usual repairing procedure, our dentist removes these infected areas to prevent further progression of the cavitation and its filled to provide protection and restore function of the tooth. A local anaesthesia is administered to make the experience. Teeth cavitation is one of the most prevalent problems in the World. Its very influenced by diet, hygiene habits. It can lead to sensitivities, unbearable pain and further untreated defects can cause complications that may even lead to systemic problems. Dental caries need to be treated at the earliest. These are best treated at an early onset when the damage is not extensive. In a usual repairing procedure, our dentist removes these infected areas to prevent further progression of the cavitation and its filled to provide protection and restore function of the tooth. A local anaesthesia is administered to make the experience non painful and comfortable.\r\n\r\nFillings are broadly tooth coloured and metal based. Composite restorations are tooth coloured fillings. They are resin based and can be matched to the existing tooth colour to obtain almost tooth like appearance, and also provides matching strengths. They attach to the tooth surface via a micromechanical bond. Metal fillings are Amalgam fillings. They are less used these days and are provided only in\r\n\r\nMetal fillings are Amalgam fillings. They are less used these days and are provided only in situation deemed required.\r\n\r\nGlass Ionomer Cements GIC are used for children, in adults involving probe areas and also used as a base under larger fillings. They bond chemically yot he tooth and have properties like white in colour, releases Flouride and is anticariogenic.\r\n\r\n[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-98 size-medium\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/pexels-photo-65055-200x300.jpeg\" alt=\"pexels-photo-65055\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />[/one_third_last]\r\n<h3>ROOT CANAL TREATMENT</h3>\r\n<p id=\"root-canal\">[one_half]<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-98 size-medium\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/pexels-photo-65055-200x300.jpeg\" alt=\"pexels-photo-65055\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />[/one_half]</p>\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<p id=\"root-canal\">If the dental caries progresses further into tooth and no intervention is seeked, it can reach the innermost layer of tooth, called Pulp. The pulp contains the nerves innervating and the blood supply of the tooth. Once the cavity progresses to the pulp individuals experiences unbearable pain and are distressed.</p>\r\nThe only way to intervene and save the tooth is via Root canal procedure. This procedure involves opening the access into roots, cleaning debriding the root canals of infection and necrotic pulp and finally filling with a biocompatible root canal restoration.\r\n\r\nIts usually followed with a post and core buildup and a dental crown.\r\n\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n<h3>INLAYS &amp; ONLAYS</h3>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<p id=\"inlays-onlays\">When the dental cavity is too large that it has taken a lot of the tooth crown structure, the regular fillings can always break under pressure from chewing and biting force. For these, the better alternative is to restore with a porcelain inlay or onlay. Porcelain can withstand much heavier forces and the colour is always lasting.</p>\r\nIn this the cavity is eliminated and the tooth is prepared, impression is taken and a custom made fitting porcelain restoration is made from our lab. Its then fitted onto the tooth to provide a perfect finish.\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-95\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/car-1284643_1280-1024x450.jpg\" alt=\"car-1284643_1280\" width=\"100%\" height=\"auto\" />[/one_half_last]\r\n<p id=\"inlays-onlays\"></p>','repairing teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-revision-v1','','','2016-11-14 11:46:13','2016-11-14 11:46:13','',40,'http://silesia.dev/40-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(168,1,'2016-11-14 11:56:27','2016-11-14 11:56:27','Your teeth are an extension if your personal health and hygiene. Its essential to make the best routines and habits to keep them top notch and healthy.\r\n<h3 id=\"scaling\">SCALING &amp; POLISHING</h3>\r\n[two_third]\r\n\r\nRoutine oral prophylaxis viz. Scaling and polishing is always recommended to maintain a healthy teeth and gum status. The ADA American Dental Association recommends scaling every 6 months.\r\n\r\nDespite the best techniques of brushing and flossing habits, there may still be elements of calculus, plaque and tartar buildup on tooth surfaces especially. These are more prevalent in areas where the access is hard like crowded teeth, the last molars and between teeth. The longer they stay, the more ill effect they cause in gingiva and periodontium (gums).\r\n\r\nScaling is the first step towards eliminating the present plaque and calculus. It involves using an ultrasound tip with a water jet that helps to dislodge and remove adherent plaque and calculus on tooth surface. This is preferably followed up with surface polishing which removes external stains from the tooth.\r\n\r\n[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-98 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/pexels-photo-65055-150x150.jpeg\" alt=\"pexels-photo-65055\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />[/one_third_last]\r\n<h3 id=\"fluoride-therapy\">FLUORIDE THERAPY</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[one_third]<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-95\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/car-1284643_1280-1024x450.jpg\" alt=\"car-1284643_1280\" width=\"1024\" height=\"450\" />[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[two_third_last]\r\n\r\nFluoride helps prevent tooth decay by making the tooth more resistant to acid attacks from plaque bacteria and sugars in the mouth. Fluoride is\r\n\r\nFluoride therapy involves applying fluoride gel to tooth surface for one to four minutes. Its is indicated for infants and children between ages from 6 months upto 15 years to help strengthen and protect the teeth.\r\n\r\n[/two_third_last]','maintaining teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2016-11-14 11:56:27','2016-11-14 11:56:27','',28,'http://silesia.dev/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2016-11-14 11:57:04','2016-11-14 11:57:04','Your teeth are an extension if your personal health and hygiene. Its essential to make the best routines and habits to keep them top notch and healthy.\r\n<h3 id=\"scaling\">SCALING &amp; POLISHING</h3>\r\n[two_third]\r\n\r\nRoutine oral prophylaxis viz. Scaling and polishing is always recommended to maintain a healthy teeth and gum status. The ADA American Dental Association recommends scaling every 6 months.\r\n\r\nDespite the best techniques of brushing and flossing habits, there may still be elements of calculus, plaque and tartar buildup on tooth surfaces especially.