gy, Orthodontics (braces), Pedodontics (Pediatric dentistry) and Prosthodontics.</p>','about silesia dental','','inherit','closed','closed','','14-revision-v1','','','2016-11-23 09:34:02','2016-11-23 09:34:02','',14,'http://dev.silesiadental.com/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(240,1,'2016-11-23 09:34:07','2016-11-23 09:34:07','<p>With a passion for dentistry, Dr. Michael Formenius started Dr. Michael’s Dental Clinic in Sweden in 1982 spanning five dental centres and a dental laboratory across Stockholm. Focused on his vision of providing outstanding services in dentistry, Dr. Michael expanded to the UAE, where he currently runs three state-of- the-art multispecialty dental clinics. All three are located along Al Wasl Road (Jumeirah and Umm Suqeim).</p>\r\n<p>Since its birth in Dubai in 1997, Dr. Michael’s Dental Clinic has built an enviable place in the industry as one of the most trusted dental healthcare providers in the region.</p>\r\n<p>True to its reputation, Dr. Michael’s Dental Clinic has grown thirty times over the last fifteen years with a highly committed team of experts serving more than 40,000 patients to date. We have assembled the finest team of dentists, specialists, dental hygienists and support staff representing General dentistry, Cosmetic dentistry (Aesthetic dentistry), Oral Surgery and Implantology, Orthodontics (braces), Pedodontics (Pediatric dentistry) and Prosthodontics.</p>','about silesia dental','','inherit','closed','closed','','14-revision-v1','','','2016-11-23 09:34:07','2016-11-23 09:34:07','',14,'http://dev.silesiadental.com/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(241,1,'2016-11-23 09:49:59','2016-11-23 09:49:59','','background-about-us','','inherit','open','closed','','background-about-us','','','2016-11-23 09:49:59','2016-11-23 09:49:59','',14,'http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/Background-About-Us.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(242,1,'2016-11-23 10:11:31','2016-11-23 10:11:31','<h3 id=\"scaling\">SCALING &amp; POLISHING</h3>\r\n[two_third]\r\n\r\nRoutine oral prophylaxis viz. Scaling and polishing is always recommended to maintain a healthy teeth and gum status. The ADA American Dental Association recommends scaling every 6 months.\r\n\r\nDespite the best techniques of brushing and flossing habits, there may still be elements of calculus, plaque and tartar buildup on tooth surfaces especially. These are more prevalent in areas where the access is hard like crowded teeth, the last molars and between teeth. The longer they stay, the more ill effect they cause in gingiva and periodontium (gums).\r\n\r\nScaling is the first step towards eliminating the present plaque and calculus. It involves using an ultrasound tip with a water jet that helps to dislodge and remove adherent plaque and calculus on tooth surface. This is preferably followed up with surface polishing which removes external stains from the tooth.\r\n\r\n[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-98 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/pexels-photo-65055-150x150.jpeg\" alt=\"pexels-photo-65055\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />[/one_third_last]\r\n<h3 id=\"fluoride-therapy\">FLUORIDE THERAPY</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[one_third]<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-95\" src=\"http://dev.silesiadental.com/app/uploads/2016/11/car-1284643_1280-1024x450.jpg\" alt=\"car-1284643_1280\" width=\"100%\" height=\"auto\" />[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[two_third_last]\r\n\r\nFluoride helps prevent tooth decay by making the tooth more resistant to acid attacks from plaque bacteria and sugars in the mouth. Fluoride is\r\n\r\nFluoride therapy involves applying fluoride gel to tooth surface for one to four minutes. Its is indicated for infants and children between ages from 6 months upto 15 years to help strengthen and protect the teeth.\r\n\r\n[/two_third_last]','Maintaining Teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2016-11-23 10:11:31','2016-11-23 10: