n and esthetics. If the extracted tooth space is left empty long, it leads to bone loss of that area and eruption of the opposing tooth into the space.\r\n\r\nThis is countered by replacing them with viable modern alternatives like dental bridges, crowns and dental implant.\r\n<h2>Crowns and Bridges</h2>\r\n<p id=\"crowns-bridges\">Crowns and bridges (Fixed Partial Denture) are custom made to fit the dimensions and functionality of the tooth. They come in variations:</p>\r\n<strong>1. Emax crown (All Porcelain crowns)</strong> These are full porcelain crowns and are strong and provide superiormost esthetics than any other alternatives.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Zircon crown</strong> These are indicative in areas requiring more strength to withstand heavier forces. The core is buildup with Zirconia (superior strength and white in colour) and is covered with porcelain. The are of excellent esthtic value.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Porcelain Fused to Metal crown (PFM)</strong> These crowns are made with a metal core which provides strength and covered by porcelain to match tooth colour.','Replacing Teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2016-11-23 11:26:51','2016-11-23 11:26:51','',42,'http://dev.silesiadental.com/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(253,1,'2016-11-23 11:30:18','2016-11-23 11:30:18','<h2>Fillings</h2>\r\n<p id=\"fillings\">Teeth cavitation is one of the most prevalent problems in the World. Its very influenced by diet, hygiene habits. It can lead to sensitivities, unbearable pain and further untreated defects can cause complications that may even lead to systemic problems.</p>\r\nDental caries need to be treated at the earliest. These are best treated at an early onset when the damage is not extensive. In a usual repairing procedure, our dentist removes these infected areas to prevent further progression of the cavitation and its filled to provide protection and restore function of the tooth. A local anaesthesia is administered to make the experience. Teeth cavitation is one of the most prevalent problems in the World. Its very influenced by diet, hygiene habits. It can lead to sensitivities, unbearable pain and further untreated defects can cause complications that may even lead to systemic problems. Dental caries need to be treated at the earliest. These are best treated at an early onset when the damage is not extensive. In a usual repairing procedure, our dentist removes these infected areas to prevent further progression of the cavitation and its filled to provide protection and restore function of the tooth. A local anaesthesia is administered to make the experience non painful and comfortable.\r\n\r\nFillings are broadly tooth coloured and metal based. Composite restorations are tooth coloured fillings. They are resin based and can be matched to the existing tooth colour to obtain almost tooth like appearance, and also provides matching strengths. They attach to the tooth surface via a micromechanical bond. Metal fillings are Amalgam fillings. They are less used these days and are provided only in\r\n\r\nMetal fillings are Amalgam fillings. They are less used these days and are provided only in situation deemed required.\r\n\r\nGlass Ionomer Cements GIC are used for children, in adults involving probe areas and also used as a base under larger fillings. They bond chemically yot he tooth and have properties like white in colour, releases Flouride and is anticariogenic.\r\n<h2>Root Canal Treatment</h2>\r\n<p id=\"root-canal\">If the dental caries progresses further into tooth and no intervention is seeked, it can reach the innermost layer of tooth, called Pulp. The pulp contains the nerves innervating and the blood supply of the tooth. Once the cavity progresses to the pulp individuals experiences unbearable pain and are distressed.</p>\r\nThe only way to intervene and save the tooth is via Root canal procedure. This procedure involves opening the access into roots, cleaning debriding the root canals of infection and necrotic pulp and finally filling with a biocompatible root canal restoration.\r\n\r\nIts usually followed with a post and core buildup and a dental crown.\r\n<h2>Inlays &amp; Onlays</h2>\r\n<p id=\"inlays-onlays\">When the dental cavity is too large that it has taken a lot of the tooth crown structure, the regular fillings can always break under pressure from chewing and biting force. For these, the better alternative is to restore with a porcelain inlay or onlay. Porcelain can withstand much heavier forces and the colour is always lasting.</p>\r\nIn this the cavity is eliminated and the tooth is prepared, impression is taken and a custom made fitting porcelain restoration is made from our lab. Its then fitted onto the tooth to provide a perfect finish.\r\n<p id=\"inlays-onlays\"></p>','Repairing Teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-revision-v1','','','2016-11-23 11:30:18','2016-11-23 11:30:18','',40,'http://dev.silesiadental.com/40-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(254,1,'2016-11-23 11:31:59','2016-11-23 11:31:59','<h2>General Extractions</h2>\r\n<p id=\"general-extraction\">When the teeth is beyond repair, it needs to be removed before it may cause a more severe sequelae that in turn gives rise to pain, swelling and discomfort. In some cases, it may be necessary to remove a tooth to facilitate Orthodontic treatment.</p>\r\nAt Silesia dental clinic, you are in expert hands who extract teeth with utmost care and almost painlessly. All extraction are done with local anaesthesia.\r\n<h2>Surgical removal</h2>\r\n<p id=\"surgical-removal\">This requires a surgical incision into the gum in order to access the indicated tooth to be removed. Most common are impacted wisdom teeth. They remain within the jaw bone and require to be removed surgically.</p>\r\nSutures may be placed for closure and healthier healing of the extraction site. Medications are prescribed for easing post operative discomforts, based on the extent of the procedure.','Removing Teeth','','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision-v1','','','2016-11-23 11:31:59','2016-11-23 11:31:59','',38,'http://dev.silesiadental.com/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
